      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BLANTONS RUN (4) resumes and scored a good win at her final run last preparation in a 65 at Ipswich over 1200m. Finds easier and will jump from an inside barrier. Just has to be tuned up to take this out. CHINCHILLA AHEAD (2) also resumes and started the last campaign in good style placing over 1200m at this track. Has trialled well and is in the right yard. A bold run is likely. Stablemate NONDISCLOSURE (1) resumes and has switched stables. Will race over further but jumps from the rail and 2x winning rider Butler stays aboard. The betting will be key. CHARMED PASSAGE (5) peaks and he'd be some hope with a repeat of his effort here two back. LUCIFER'S WAY (3) resumes for the new yard with the blinkers on for the first time. He has placed fresh and has the ability.",
